You police are useless!

284
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:17,960
They hacked us and
infiltrated the surveillance system.

285
00:18:18,120 --> 00:18:18,720
So...

286
00:18:18,760 --> 00:18:20,280
Without Skyeye,

287
00:18:20,360 --> 00:18:21,816
we can't fight crimes anymore, Is that it?

288
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:23,720
Before we had all this technology,

289
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:25,760
how did the police do their jobs?

290
00:18:26,560 --> 00:18:27,840
It was my mistake.

291
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:29,280
I'll catch them next time.

292
00:18:29,360 --> 00:18:30,520
Even if there's a next time,

293
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:33,120
they'll probably still
counter our every move.

294
00:18:33,160 --> 00:18:34,680
So tell me, what do we do?

295
00:18:35,040 --> 00:18:36,240
If they stop now,

296
00:18:36,320 --> 00:18:37,520
where's our breakthrough?

297
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:39,680
Sorry, sir.

298
00:18:40,040 --> 00:18:42,360
What's the progress from cyber division?

299
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:44,680
We've patched the
intrusion point and code bugs,

300
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:46,400
but no progress on reverse tracking.

301
00:18:49,600 --> 00:18:50,920
To catch a cunning fox,

302
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:52,400
we need an experienced hunter.

303
00:18:56,040 --> 00:18:57,080
Are you suggesting

304
00:18:57,480 --> 00:18:58,880
bringing back Wong?

305
00:19:03,760 --> 00:19:04,880
I know he's your old boss.

306
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:06,856
But this is the era of A.I. tracking.

307
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:08,960
And they've just exploited its weakness.

308
00:19:10,200 --> 00:19:11,376
There are flaws in the network

309
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:12,680
and surveillance equipment,

310
00:19:12,760 --> 00:19:13,840
but S.P.A.I.S. is flawless.

311
00:19:13,920 --> 00:19:15,376
You stopped S.P.A.I.S.
learning from real operations.

312
00:19:15,400 --> 00:19:16,480
You let your phone

313
00:19:16,560 --> 00:19:18,040
tell you how to do your job?

314
00:19:18,120 --> 00:19:19,136
That doesn't mean bringing in a fossil

315
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:20,216
will fix the police's image.

316
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:21,240
Captain.

317
00:19:22,080 --> 00:19:24,920
I don't care if we use
fossil or Spice Girl,

318
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:27,000
Find them, catch them.

319
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:28,560
Do your job.

320
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:33,320
Jeez, Guoguo,

321
00:19:33,480 --> 00:19:35,760
have you seen Wong's file?

322
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:37,320
He's incredible.

323
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:39,280
Multiple commendations.

324
00:19:40,080 --> 00:19:42,240
Special Ops all-around champion.

325
00:19:42,280 --> 00:19:43,920
Police hand-to-hand combat champion.

326
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:45,240
Five years straight!

327
00:19:45,720 --> 00:19:46,936
Proficient in firearms, surveillance,

328
00:19:46,960 --> 00:19:48,480
infiltration,

329
00:19:48,560 --> 00:19:49,880
intelligence gathering.

330
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:51,720
He's gone undercover in drug cartels

331
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:54,120
and organ trafficking rings.

332
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:56,440
Restrained, low-profile.

333
00:19:56,520 --> 00:19:57,960
Skilled at blending in.

334
00:19:58,560 --> 00:19:59,800
Hobby...

335
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,000
Making up call signs.

336
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:04,480
This says his career's single stain is

337
00:20:04,560 --> 00:20:09,440
a major personal mistake that killed
his partner.

338
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:23,280
Write down which dog pees and poos first.

339
00:20:23,520 --> 00:20:24,960
Is that really him?

340
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:29,200
Hi.

341
00:20:29,240 --> 00:20:30,240
Have you find it?

342
00:20:30,400 --> 00:20:31,400
Nope.

343
00:20:32,280 --> 00:20:34,880
Everyone else is on
the field for the big case

344
00:20:35,160 --> 00:20:37,360
and I have no idea what I'm doing.

345
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:38,800
Observing someone's retirement?

346
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:39,880
Be patient.

347
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:41,760
Maybe captain's looking out for you.

348
00:20:41,800 --> 00:20:43,456
Perhaps we're not ready for the field yet.

349
00:20:43,480 --> 00:20:44,480
I'll call you later.

350
00:21:17,920 --> 00:21:19,440
A training drill on a geezer like me?

351
00:21:20,960 --> 00:21:22,360
Sir, are you talking to me?

352
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:27,200
Why are you following me?

353
00:21:30,320 --> 00:21:32,000
You're mistaking me for someone else.

354
00:21:34,320 --> 00:21:35,400
You don't know me?

355
00:21:37,080 --> 00:21:38,120
I don't.

356
00:21:40,240 --> 00:21:41,320
Do you need something?

357
00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:45,520
You weren't tailing me
in a jacket in reverse?

358
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:49,000
Can you sit elsewhere?

359
00:21:58,280 --> 00:21:59,840
Sorry. It's fine.

360
00:22:07,320 --> 00:22:09,920
At 14:23, you reached the first target,

361
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:12,360
which was the pet shop, Up to now

362
00:22:12,560 --> 00:22:14,920
you've tailed me for 4
hours and 17 minutes.

363
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:16,680
You changed your outfit three times,

364
00:22:17,760 --> 00:22:19,360
and stopped 9 times to jot notes.

365
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:21,960
On the bus, you had a colleague help you.

366
00:22:23,520 --> 00:22:24,720
Watch it. Pardon me.

367
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:26,760
Am I right, He Qiuguo?

368
00:22:34,320 --> 00:22:36,800
That look just gave you away.

369
00:22:39,920 --> 00:22:41,920
You remember me, Uncle Wong.

370
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:44,080
We haven't met since I was 8.

371
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:47,640
I heard you joined the force

372
00:22:47,840 --> 00:22:49,480
and inherited your father's badge number.

373
00:22:50,320 --> 00:22:51,640
He would be proud.

374
00:22:54,120 --> 00:22:56,160
How'd you know when I was at the pet shop?

375
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:58,560
I only say it because you ask about it.

376
00:22:59,520 --> 00:23:00,400
First of all,

377
00:23:00,520 --> 00:23:01,720
never throw away your notes.

378
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:02,600
Second,

379
00:23:02,680 --> 00:23:05,416
dog walking time, leaving work, and
boarding the bus were all inaccurate.

380
00:23:05,440 --> 00:23:07,720
The order of dogs pee and poo is a mess.

381
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:09,080
Which one was the sixth to poop?

382
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:11,360
Al Paca-paca, the poodle.

383
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:19,280
It'd be my mistake if I didn't pick it up.

384
00:23:19,360 --> 00:23:21,280
Confuse my memory if I did.

385
00:23:21,360 --> 00:23:22,360
Not bad.

386
00:23:22,920 --> 00:23:24,480
You said my colleague was on the bus.

387
00:23:24,560 --> 00:23:25,560
Why do you say that?

388
00:23:26,160 --> 00:23:27,160
Oh, I see.

389
00:23:28,120 --> 00:23:30,520
This isn't training. You're checking

390
00:23:30,600 --> 00:23:31,720
if I've still got it.

391
00:23:37,560 --> 00:23:40,600
You two tailed me for 4
hours at that skill level.

392
00:23:40,680 --> 00:23:42,080
Who gave you the confidence?

393
00:23:58,680 --> 00:24:00,000
You know Madam Wang, right?

394
00:24:00,080 --> 00:24:01,096
Long time no see, Officer Wong.

395
00:24:01,120 --> 00:24:02,520
This is inspector Wu Yaolei.

396
00:24:03,160 --> 00:24:04,160
Hi.

397
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:06,440
Let me do it.

398
00:24:06,520 --> 00:24:07,520
No.

399
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:13,040
You call yourself a cop?

400
00:24:13,120 --> 00:24:15,000
No wonder I felt that old man touched me.

401
00:24:15,240 --> 00:24:16,640
Sound like you're proud of it.

402
00:24:18,280 --> 00:24:20,000
So the partner

403
00:24:20,640 --> 00:24:21,880
who died on duty...

404
00:24:22,680 --> 00:24:23,680
That was your dad?

405
00:24:26,400 --> 00:24:27,400
Back off.

406
00:24:29,600 --> 00:24:31,800
These are footage we
gathered from the scene.

407
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:32,720
This footage is

408
00:24:32,840 --> 00:24:35,080
Wynn's feed before hackers cut it.

409
00:24:43,200 --> 00:24:44,920
Just play the last 15 seconds, please.

410
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:53,960
Play it again.

411
00:25:04,560 --> 00:25:05,560
Once more.

412
00:25:21,480 --> 00:25:22,480
Stop.

413
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:41,320
How did you spot them?

414
00:25:41,400 --> 00:25:43,720
They peeked at cameras when they entered.

415
00:25:45,040 --> 00:25:46,216
They must have scouted beforehand

416
00:25:46,240 --> 00:25:47,376
and knew where the cameras were.

417
00:25:47,400 --> 00:25:48,280
Why'd they look, then?

418
00:25:48,360 --> 00:25:50,040
To see if the cameras were still on.

419
00:25:52,440 --> 00:25:53,600
Once the cameras were cut,

420
00:25:53,680 --> 00:25:54,960
they changed their disguises.

421
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:57,720
Didn't they?

422
00:26:08,240 --> 00:26:09,240
Xiwang.

423
00:26:17,520 --> 00:26:19,720
Old man pissed over the change of plans?

424
00:26:19,800 --> 00:26:20,800
What do you think?

425
00:26:23,120 --> 00:26:24,480
Go console him.

426
00:26:25,840 --> 00:26:27,680
Godfather... We all made it back safely.

427
00:26:27,760 --> 00:26:29,040
Hell of a day, wasn't it?

428
00:26:29,120 --> 00:26:30,560
You little shit. I can explain.

429
00:26:32,120 --> 00:26:33,800
You almost got everyone killed.

430
00:26:33,880 --> 00:26:35,400
That wasn't part of the plan.

431
00:26:37,920 --> 00:26:39,080
But we got the job done.

432
00:26:40,200 --> 00:26:41,880
With a bonus, no less.

433
00:26:43,320 --> 00:26:44,320
What bonus?

434
00:26:44,400 --> 00:26:45,600
I only saw mistakes.

435
00:26:47,680 --> 00:26:48,960
All these years,

436
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:50,520
I've never been caught on camera.

437
00:26:50,760 --> 00:26:51,840
Now I have,

438
00:26:52,280 --> 00:26:53,360
you little shit!

439
00:26:53,920 --> 00:26:55,280
It'll be fine, I'll handle it.

440
00:26:55,760 --> 00:26:56,960
You're a little shit too.

441
00:26:58,400 --> 00:26:59,440
Just let go.

442
00:27:00,040 --> 00:27:01,320
Let us call the shots for once.

443
00:27:06,440 --> 00:27:07,440
Let go?

444
00:27:15,080 --> 00:27:16,080
Let go.

445
00:27:33,520 --> 00:27:35,680
What I should be scared of now?

446
00:27:39,480 --> 00:27:41,320
You wouldn't understand it anyway.

447
00:27:44,680 --> 00:27:45,880
Let me tell you

448
00:27:46,280 --> 00:27:48,120
what you should fear.

449
00:27:56,440 --> 00:27:57,440
Godfather.

450
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:06,000
Xiwang.

451
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:08,720
Even you're turning on me.

452
00:28:11,400 --> 00:28:12,400
Godfather.

453
00:28:12,560 --> 00:28:14,280
Don't be mad. You little shit.

454
00:28:14,880 --> 00:28:16,480
For decades, no one's had a photo of me.

455
00:28:16,560 --> 00:28:17,736
I now got shot because of you!

456
00:28:17,760 --> 00:28:19,016
That's more than 10 billion sweet HKD.

457
00:28:19,040 --> 00:28:20,320
They knew they were wrong.

458
00:28:20,400 --> 00:28:21,760
We can all live our dreams.

459
00:28:21,840 --> 00:28:24,000
What 10 billion? Is that in cash?

460
00:28:24,080 --> 00:28:25,080
Godfather, don't be mad.

461
00:28:31,600 --> 00:28:32,600
That tall guy.

462
00:28:32,680 --> 00:28:34,360
The walking lightning rod changed outfits.

463
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:35,520
Eyes on the screen.

464
00:28:35,640 --> 00:28:36,640
Lightning Rod.

465
00:28:37,280 --> 00:28:38,440
Remember his characteristics.

466
00:28:39,440 --> 00:28:40,536
This guy, grinding his teeth.

467
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:41,560
Number 2, number 2.

468
00:28:41,960 --> 00:28:43,320
Found the one with the earrings.

469
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:44,880
That's right. That's him.

470
00:28:45,360 --> 00:28:46,120
Send it.

471
00:28:46,200 --> 00:28:47,656
On the screen, that's Lil Puppy no. 2.

472
00:28:47,680 --> 00:28:48,480
Lightning Rod 3 spotted,

473
00:28:48,640 --> 00:28:49,520
not very clear though.

474
00:28:49,600 --> 00:28:50,696
I've got a decent shot over here.

475
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:51,880
Very good, very good.

476
00:28:51,960 --> 00:28:52,880
Pretty Face number 2,

477
00:28:52,960 --> 00:28:53,920
wearing a small mustache. Got it.

478
00:28:53,960 --> 00:28:54,640
I got Pretty Face number 3.

479
00:28:54,720 --> 00:28:56,256
The squatting one. He changed disguises.

480
00:28:56,280 --> 00:28:58,000
How many fake mustaches does he have?

481
00:29:03,240 --> 00:29:04,520
Sir, I think this one is...

482
00:29:04,600 --> 00:29:05,600
Pretty Face number 4.

483
00:29:06,400 --> 00:29:08,600
I've seen this coat somewhere.

484
00:29:11,040 --> 00:29:12,120
Someone gave it to him!

485
00:29:12,560 --> 00:29:13,360
Everybody, listen up.

486
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:14,520
There's one more person.

487
00:29:14,720 --> 00:29:16,720
Cast everything you
find to the main screen.

488
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:17,920
Yes, sir.

489
00:29:34,320 --> 00:29:35,560
Police. Police.

490
00:29:36,680 --> 00:29:37,680
Sorry.

491
00:29:56,680 --> 00:29:57,680
Xiwang.

492
00:30:00,160 --> 00:30:01,640
You saved my life once.

493
00:30:04,240 --> 00:30:05,960
I value this life very much.

494
00:30:08,240 --> 00:30:10,400
I don't want anything to happen to you all.

495
00:30:12,800 --> 00:30:13,840
Got that?

496
00:30:14,960 --> 00:30:15,960
Yes.

497
00:30:16,840 --> 00:30:17,840
Got it.

498
00:30:18,440 --> 00:30:19,440
We're with you,

499
00:30:19,800 --> 00:30:20,800
live or die.

500
00:30:29,480 --> 00:30:30,640
I don't want to die.

501
00:30:33,760 --> 00:30:37,120
I want all of us to enjoy our lives.

502
00:30:41,160 --> 00:30:43,040
Ms. Sun, the lobby café barista,

503
00:30:43,120 --> 00:30:44,720
took this photo that afternoon.

504
00:30:45,520 --> 00:30:47,920
This is very likely the
fifth person at Wynn.

505
00:30:48,440 --> 00:30:50,080
Do we have any idea of his identity?

506
00:30:50,680 --> 00:30:52,560
Sorry sir, not yet.

507
00:30:55,240 --> 00:30:58,160
In the late 80s,
there was a wanted foreign ex-special force

508
00:30:59,840 --> 00:31:01,400
known as "The Shadow".

509
00:31:01,520 --> 00:31:04,960
He served in an elite assassination squad.

510
00:31:05,040 --> 00:31:06,720
During the war, he disguised himself

511
00:31:06,800 --> 00:31:08,640
to infiltrate military
and political targets.

512
00:31:08,920 --> 00:31:10,840
His kills were executed
up close with a knife.

513
00:31:10,920 --> 00:31:11,960
And he always got away.

514
00:31:12,080 --> 00:31:14,840
Later, he fled here to seek greater wealth.

515
00:31:15,040 --> 00:31:17,400
He planned more than a dozen bank heists

516
00:31:17,520 --> 00:31:19,320
and evaded three manhunts

517
00:31:19,560 --> 00:31:21,760
before vanishing without a trace in 1999.

518
00:31:22,280 --> 00:31:24,080
This guy could be the Shadow

519
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:26,840
coming out of retirement.

520
00:31:27,400 --> 00:31:28,240
I remember him.

521
00:31:28,360 --> 00:31:29,680
What's your next step?

522
00:31:29,760 --> 00:31:32,440
This photo isn't enough
for facial recognition.

523
00:31:32,560 --> 00:31:33,800
We plan to increase manpower

524
00:31:33,880 --> 00:31:35,320
for a comprehensive sweep.

525
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:36,240
Area?

526
00:31:36,320 --> 00:31:38,400
We have few shots of
his accomplice's vehicle.

527
00:31:38,440 --> 00:31:40,160
These were all taken in the Old Town area.

528
00:31:40,240 --> 00:31:40,920
It's a large area.

529
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:42,600
I suggest a two-pronged approach.

530
00:31:42,640 --> 00:31:44,160
Conduct an open sweep for diversion

531
00:31:44,200 --> 00:31:46,040
while dispatching a
covert surveillance team.

532
00:31:46,160 --> 00:31:47,160
Officer Wong.

533
00:31:47,840 --> 00:31:49,336
There's no covert
surveillance team anymore.

534
00:31:49,360 --> 00:31:50,360
Not anymore?

535
00:31:50,560 --> 00:31:52,840
With today's surveillance network and A.I.,

536
00:31:53,120 --> 00:31:55,080
traditional covert surveillance teams

537
00:31:55,280 --> 00:31:56,760
are hardly ever needed.

538
00:32:01,120 --> 00:32:02,320
Small suggestion

539
00:32:02,520 --> 00:32:03,600
for ground surveillance.

540
00:32:03,680 --> 00:32:06,520
You should use your
most inconspicuous officers.

541
00:32:06,600 --> 00:32:08,400
Preferably ones suspects
haven't seen before.

542
00:32:14,480 --> 00:32:15,280
Officer Wong,

543
00:32:15,440 --> 00:32:18,680
why don't you help us
set up a temporary team?

544
00:32:21,040 --> 00:32:23,360
A covert team put together last-minute

545
00:32:23,640 --> 00:32:25,080
won't be as effective as

546
00:32:25,160 --> 00:32:26,160
a comprehensive approach.

547
00:32:35,360 --> 00:32:36,360
Little girl.

548
00:32:37,080 --> 00:32:38,720
Stay in your lane out there.

549
00:32:39,080 --> 00:32:40,480
Leave the arresting to us.

550
00:32:40,760 --> 00:32:41,400
Remember that.

551
00:32:41,480 --> 00:32:43,840
Little girl can show off all she wants.

552
00:32:44,360 --> 00:32:47,280
I'm just worried that showing off
will get to her head

553
00:32:47,360 --> 00:32:48,520
and let them slip away again.

554
00:32:52,360 --> 00:32:54,560
Why did someone so tiny become a cop?

555
00:32:54,800 --> 00:32:56,680
Her old man was a cop.

556
00:32:56,760 --> 00:32:59,400
Doesn't she know she's just a poster child?

557
00:32:59,840 --> 00:33:01,240
Can't even crack a smile.

558
00:33:04,400 --> 00:33:06,136
What business is it
of yours that I'm a cop?

559
00:33:06,160 --> 00:33:07,680
I earned my spot in the Police Force.

560
00:33:07,760 --> 00:33:08,800
How dare you.

561
00:33:09,720 --> 00:33:12,120
Don't forget,
it was you idiots who let them get away.

562
00:33:13,720 --> 00:33:14,480
C'mon, I'm the suspect.

563
00:33:14,560 --> 00:33:16,080
Catch me. C'mon.

564
00:33:22,240 --> 00:33:23,760
Field agent? Yeah, right.

565
00:33:42,320 --> 00:33:43,080
Come on.

566
00:33:43,160 --> 00:33:44,160
C'mon, get him.

567
00:33:59,880 --> 00:34:01,296
In a place like the detective squad,

568
00:34:01,320 --> 00:34:02,840
a little spar will earn you respect.

569
00:34:03,200 --> 00:34:04,920
They'll watch your back out there.

570
00:34:09,120 --> 00:34:10,679
No one in this place thinks

571
00:34:10,760 --> 00:34:12,960
a woman could be the
first to kick down a door.

572
00:34:13,719 --> 00:34:16,120
The first one can catch a bullet, too.

573
00:34:16,199 --> 00:34:17,199
So what?

574
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:18,520
I'm not afraid to die.

575
00:34:18,600 --> 00:34:19,960
But they don't want you to die.

576
00:34:20,600 --> 00:34:22,080
My life isn't their concern.

577
00:34:22,800 --> 00:34:24,215
They do care about their colleagues' lives.

578
00:34:24,239 --> 00:34:25,639
No one sees me as a colleague.

579
00:34:32,320 --> 00:34:33,320
Old friend...

580
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:36,000
Guoguo's all grown up.

581
00:34:37,920 --> 00:34:38,960
She's just like you.

582
00:34:40,880 --> 00:34:43,679
But I can tell she's
not happy in the squad.

583
00:34:46,199 --> 00:34:47,719
That short fuse of hers

584
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:49,400
might get her in trouble

585
00:34:50,320 --> 00:34:51,320
out on the field.

586
00:34:52,320 --> 00:34:53,400
Freeze. Police.

587
00:35:01,320 --> 00:35:02,480
Rest assured.

588
00:35:02,560 --> 00:35:03,840
I'll look after her.

589
00:35:48,520 --> 00:35:49,520
I'll do it.

590
00:35:49,920 --> 00:35:51,440
I'll train a covert surveillance team.

591
00:35:51,720 --> 00:35:52,720
Let's catch him.

592
00:36:04,320 --> 00:36:06,640
How nice of Captain Wu to send so many.

593
00:36:17,640 --> 00:36:18,880
Thank you. Goodbye.

594
00:36:20,680 --> 00:36:21,680
You look like a cop.

595
00:36:23,920 --> 00:36:25,160
Thanks.

596
00:36:25,840 --> 00:36:28,440
We're dealing with an old fox.

597
00:36:28,520 --> 00:36:29,960
An old-school thief.

598
00:36:30,400 --> 00:36:32,040
That's why I'm going to train you

599
00:36:32,120 --> 00:36:33,360
to become old-school hunters.

600
00:36:33,800 --> 00:36:34,800
Come.

601
00:36:35,320 --> 00:36:36,560
During surveillance,

602
00:36:36,640 --> 00:36:38,880
develop an instinct to watch and memorize.

603
00:36:39,840 --> 00:36:41,760
One glance. That's all you get.

604
00:36:41,800 --> 00:36:42,720
Focus on key characteristics.

605
00:36:42,800 --> 00:36:45,720
Remember prominent and permanent features.

606
00:36:46,840 --> 00:36:48,016
I had my hands on my hips just now.

607
00:36:48,040 --> 00:36:49,360
Which two fingers

608
00:36:49,720 --> 00:36:50,720
were in my pockets?

609
00:36:50,920 --> 00:36:51,640
Left forefinger.

610
00:36:51,720 --> 00:36:52,880
Right middle finger.

611
00:37:00,400 --> 00:37:02,320
A surveillance team is an entity.

612
00:37:02,600 --> 00:37:04,240
It takes every member

613
00:37:04,360 --> 00:37:05,600
to complete a mission.

614
00:37:07,280 --> 00:37:08,280
Let's go.

615
00:37:09,640 --> 00:37:10,640
Guoguo.

616
00:37:13,400 --> 00:37:14,400
Get in.

617
00:37:16,880 --> 00:37:19,280
Starting today, you
need to blend into the city.

618
00:37:19,920 --> 00:37:21,080
Let's put theory into action.

619
00:37:21,640 --> 00:37:23,160
Doghead calling Animal Paradise.

620
00:37:23,320 --> 00:37:24,000
Officer Wong,

621
00:37:24,280 --> 00:37:25,320
what did you say?

622
00:37:25,360 --> 00:37:26,120
Doghead.

623
00:37:26,240 --> 00:37:27,080
That's me.

624
00:37:27,160 --> 00:37:28,560
My call sign is Doghead.

625
00:37:28,760 --> 00:37:30,600
Adorable Unit's on site.

626
00:37:30,920 --> 00:37:32,480
I'll give your call signs now.

627
00:37:32,720 --> 00:37:33,880
Liu, you're Al Paca-paca.

628
00:37:34,840 --> 00:37:36,200
Can I get another one?

629
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:38,560
I'll make it simpler. Alpaca.

630
00:37:39,760 --> 00:37:40,560
Okay.

631
00:37:40,640 --> 00:37:42,120
Wanwan... You're Tofu.

632
00:37:42,240 --> 00:37:43,800
Yang Zhiwei... Rice Noodles.

633
00:37:44,000 --> 00:37:45,360
Ting... Pudding.

634
00:37:45,480 --> 00:37:47,240
Sun Xu... Potsticker.

635
00:37:47,320 --> 00:37:48,960
Liao Qihang... Eggy.

636
00:37:49,040 --> 00:37:50,760
Qiao Weidong... Lucky.

637
00:37:50,920 --> 00:37:52,120
Song Keyu...

638
00:37:52,520 --> 00:37:53,600
Pork Bun.

639
00:37:54,040 --> 00:37:55,040
Hello.

640
00:37:55,520 --> 00:37:56,840
Isn't that body shaming?

641
00:37:56,920 --> 00:37:58,040
It's a local specialty.

642
00:37:58,400 --> 00:37:59,480
This is a foodie squad.

643
00:37:59,920 --> 00:38:01,280
Better than my old unit.

644
00:38:01,680 --> 00:38:02,680
He Qiuguo...

645
00:38:03,560 --> 00:38:04,560
Little Flower Piggy.

646
00:38:04,880 --> 00:38:05,440
Can I change it?

647
00:38:05,520 --> 00:38:06,920
I'll drop "Little".

648
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:09,240
Then drop "Flower".

649
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:18,000
Patience.

650
00:38:18,080 --> 00:38:19,640
You're my ace in the hole.

651
00:38:20,400 --> 00:38:21,600
Like I believe you.

652
00:38:25,160 --> 00:38:25,840
It's fine.

653
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:27,320
I'm used to being benched.

654
00:38:28,440 --> 00:38:29,280
Boss,

655
00:38:29,400 --> 00:38:30,520
how much for this?

656
00:38:31,840 --> 00:38:32,520
Where'd you get this?

657
00:38:32,560 --> 00:38:34,520
None of your business.
Pay her and send her off.

658
00:38:37,160 --> 00:38:38,040
Can I try it?

659
00:38:38,120 --> 00:38:38,880
Hey...

660
00:38:38,960 --> 00:38:41,040
Don't stare like they're suspects.

661
00:38:43,680 --> 00:38:44,680
Pull over.

662
00:38:58,360 --> 00:39:00,520
Am I exposed?

663
00:39:00,760 --> 00:39:02,520
This is your third time in the same spot

664
00:39:02,600 --> 00:39:03,600
in the same outfit

665
00:39:03,680 --> 00:39:05,920
using the same hand to drink the same way.

666
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:08,040
Your water is stuck at the same amount.

667
00:39:08,640 --> 00:39:10,520
I'm worried I'd need to pee.

668
00:39:10,560 --> 00:39:11,920
Dehydration kills you too.

669
00:39:12,280 --> 00:39:13,280
Drink.

670
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:44,680
There's 10 billion at stake.

671
00:39:45,040 --> 00:39:47,320
Once we get it, we're set for life.

672
00:39:47,440 --> 00:39:48,640
It's just one last time.

673
00:39:49,360 --> 00:39:52,000
That's what you all think, isn't it?

674
00:39:53,000 --> 00:39:55,040
Money isn't everything.

675
00:39:55,720 --> 00:39:57,040
Life is.

676
00:39:57,600 --> 00:40:00,440
Different time, different game.

677
00:40:05,960 --> 00:40:09,240
If I let you plan the next mission...

678
00:40:09,680 --> 00:40:10,960
You know what you're doing?

679
00:40:27,760 --> 00:40:28,760
Simon.

680
00:40:29,320 --> 00:40:30,320
Dad.

681
00:40:30,600 --> 00:40:31,600
Simon.

682
00:40:33,200 --> 00:40:34,120
Dad.

683
00:40:34,200 --> 00:40:35,200
Xiwang

684
00:40:36,640 --> 00:40:37,640
You've grown so much.

685
00:40:37,960 --> 00:40:39,080
Come. Come on.

686
00:40:42,720 --> 00:40:43,800
Thanks, daddy!

687
00:40:45,400 --> 00:40:46,640
I have to leave for a while.

688
00:40:46,840 --> 00:40:48,120
Take good care of your brothers.

689
00:40:52,320 --> 00:40:53,640
I'll come back for you boys.

690
00:40:59,520 --> 00:41:01,560
Duan stashed 1.5 billion
USD worth of crypto.

691
00:41:01,600 --> 00:41:04,000
The server location has been found.

692
00:41:04,040 --> 00:41:05,440
We already have the decryption key,

693
00:41:05,520 --> 00:41:07,520
but the digital vault is hard to access.

694
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:09,480
Simon's hiding at the orphanage,

695
00:41:09,560 --> 00:41:10,640
making plans right now

696
00:41:13,520 --> 00:41:14,800
The orphanage is a nice place.

697
00:41:15,360 --> 00:41:16,520
It holds a lot of memories.

698
00:41:17,960 --> 00:41:19,040
I know you're all tired,

699
00:41:19,120 --> 00:41:20,800
but stay focused.

700
00:41:33,560 --> 00:41:34,280
Don't want a coffee?

701
00:41:34,360 --> 00:41:35,360
Get a pick-me-up.

702
00:41:35,400 --> 00:41:36,960
Do I look tired to you?

703
00:41:39,200 --> 00:41:40,680
Have you thought about

704
00:41:40,920 --> 00:41:42,000
killing me?

705
00:41:43,240 --> 00:41:44,280
Then you can split

706
00:41:45,000 --> 00:41:46,080
my share.

707
00:41:48,360 --> 00:41:49,920
How could we, Godfather?

708
00:41:51,280 --> 00:41:52,640
I'm old anyway.

709
00:41:53,120 --> 00:41:54,720
I don't know about the new ways.

710
00:41:58,240 --> 00:41:59,240
Am I right?

711
00:42:00,480 --> 00:42:01,520
Why'd you say

712
00:42:01,920 --> 00:42:03,160
I'm your ace in the hole?

713
00:42:11,040 --> 00:42:12,320
Are you gaslighting me?

714
00:42:14,120 --> 00:42:15,120
Gas what?

715
00:42:15,840 --> 00:42:17,016
If anyone even considers that,

716
00:42:17,040 --> 00:42:18,120
I'll kill him.

717
00:42:19,400 --> 00:42:20,800
The knife was already in your hand.

718
00:42:21,680 --> 00:42:23,200
You think I didn't see that?

719
00:42:24,880 --> 00:42:26,360
Am I not good enough?

720
00:42:26,400 --> 00:42:28,200
You think I need special treatment, too?

721
00:42:28,280 --> 00:42:30,000
No. You're fine.

722
00:42:30,880 --> 00:42:32,480
You don't need special treatment.

723
00:42:35,040 --> 00:42:36,560
When the knife's in your hand...

724
00:42:37,680 --> 00:42:39,080
Don't blink.

725
00:42:40,840 --> 00:42:42,520
Be forceful,

726
00:42:47,440 --> 00:42:49,520
or it wouldn't be a clean shave.

727
00:42:52,720 --> 00:42:54,320
Then why is everyone on the field

728
00:42:54,400 --> 00:42:56,680
and I'm sitting here, getting you coffee?

729
00:42:57,440 --> 00:42:58,720
You just really want to... Yes.

730
00:42:59,920 --> 00:43:00,920
I really want to.

731
00:43:10,520 --> 00:43:12,840
But I need you here right now.

732
00:43:13,520 --> 00:43:15,360
Be my surveillance partner.

733
00:43:18,200 --> 00:43:19,240
That's an order.

734
00:43:23,640 --> 00:43:24,640
Yes, sir.

735
00:43:28,640 --> 00:43:29,640
Brother,

736
00:43:29,760 --> 00:43:31,800
if Xin hadn't held the old man back,

737
00:43:31,880 --> 00:43:33,120
he would've stabbed me.

738
00:43:33,480 --> 00:43:34,760
He really meant to kill me.

739
00:43:42,560 --> 00:43:43,560
Is it really that good?

740
00:43:44,400 --> 00:43:46,000
It's just luncheon meat and egg noodles.

741
00:43:46,120 --> 00:43:47,720
It's not easy to make.

742
00:43:50,200 --> 00:43:52,080
When I was your age,

743
00:43:52,480 --> 00:43:53,520
all I thought about was

744
00:43:53,840 --> 00:43:55,400
how to stay alive.

745
00:43:59,040 --> 00:44:00,600
I envy that you boys

746
00:44:01,160 --> 00:44:02,160
dare to dream anything,

747
00:44:03,520 --> 00:44:04,680
can dream of anything

748
00:44:05,480 --> 00:44:06,320
All I want

749
00:44:06,400 --> 00:44:08,160
is a life in peace

750
00:44:08,200 --> 00:44:09,400
with all my brothers together.

751
00:44:09,640 --> 00:44:10,720
Not scattered, like now.

752
00:44:12,360 --> 00:44:13,560
All these years,

753
00:44:13,960 --> 00:44:15,120
in order to look after me,

754
00:44:15,720 --> 00:44:18,320
you sacrificed spending
time with your brothers.

755
00:44:19,680 --> 00:44:21,160
Since the day you saved me,

756
00:44:21,240 --> 00:44:22,720
you've been protecting me.

757
00:44:23,760 --> 00:44:25,560
When all those cops were after me,

758
00:44:27,080 --> 00:44:29,560
I couldn't believe a little punk like you

759
00:44:30,240 --> 00:44:31,320
would save me.

760
00:44:32,920 --> 00:44:34,680
Then you risked your life

761
00:44:34,760 --> 00:44:36,240
to keep the bankrupt orphanage alive.

762
00:44:36,280 --> 00:44:37,280
Without you,

763
00:44:37,320 --> 00:44:38,560
we'd have starved to death.

764
00:44:44,400 --> 00:44:46,760
Eat mine too if you are so hungry.

765
00:44:52,120 --> 00:44:53,520
Out of all the kids,

766
00:44:53,600 --> 00:44:55,200
you're the one I care about the most.

767
00:44:56,080 --> 00:44:57,920
Because you're just like me.

768
00:44:59,160 --> 00:45:00,240
Simon is more like you.

769
00:45:03,280 --> 00:45:04,280
If that is so...

770
00:45:04,520 --> 00:45:06,680
He could be very dangerous.

771
00:45:13,800 --> 00:45:14,800
Eggy and Tofu,

772
00:45:14,880 --> 00:45:15,880
your date's over.

773
00:45:16,000 --> 00:45:17,240
Get changed and get to Point E.

774
00:45:18,640 --> 00:45:19,640
Pudding.

775
00:45:20,000 --> 00:45:21,240
Change and get to Point B.

776
00:45:24,360 --> 00:45:25,840
Pork Bun. Point A.

777
00:45:33,520 --> 00:45:35,640
Something's been feeling off lately.

778
00:45:36,240 --> 00:45:37,240
Therefore,

779
00:45:37,280 --> 00:45:38,280
stay away for a while.

780
00:45:38,880 --> 00:45:40,600
I can take care of myself.

781
00:46:05,040 --> 00:46:06,040
Help!

782
00:46:09,040 --> 00:46:10,040
Help me!

783
00:46:11,960 --> 00:46:12,560
No!

784
00:46:12,720 --> 00:46:14,520
Come back to the car.

785
00:46:14,680 --> 00:46:15,680
Call the police.

786
00:46:17,720 --> 00:46:18,720
I am the police.

787
00:46:23,600 --> 00:46:24,600
Leave them alone.

788
00:46:24,720 --> 00:46:25,720
Get lost.

789
00:46:27,360 --> 00:46:30,120
You're pretty cute, little missy.

790
00:46:46,080 --> 00:46:47,080
Who are you?

791
00:46:56,160 --> 00:46:57,160
Go.

792
00:47:05,840 --> 00:47:07,000
Why don't you move? Let's go.

793
00:47:11,440 --> 00:47:12,440
Drive.

794
00:47:17,080 --> 00:47:18,080
Systems off.

795
00:47:22,240 --> 00:47:24,160
Do you know you're on a mission?

796
00:47:27,080 --> 00:47:28,800
Protecting civilians is a cop's mission.

797
00:47:28,840 --> 00:47:30,400
At the right place and the right time.

798
00:47:31,640 --> 00:47:33,040
You're on an active mission.

799
00:47:33,160 --> 00:47:33,880
What's the mission?

800
00:47:33,960 --> 00:47:35,320
Operation Dinner for Officer Wong?

801
00:47:35,400 --> 00:47:36,800
Sorry, I failed the mission.

802
00:47:38,280 --> 00:47:39,280
Listen carefully.

803
00:47:39,320 --> 00:47:41,040
You are on a covert surveillance mission.

804
00:47:41,200 --> 00:47:43,720
You cannot blow your cover, no matter what.

805
00:47:43,800 --> 00:47:45,096
I didn't blow shit.
You reached for your badge.

806
00:47:45,120 --> 00:47:46,336
If the Shadow saw that, it's all over.

807
00:47:46,360 --> 00:47:48,000
And where is he?

808
00:47:48,960 --> 00:47:50,016
We've been wandering for weeks.

809
00:47:50,040 --> 00:47:51,496
It's time we actually do some real work.

810
00:47:51,520 --> 00:47:52,880
This is real work.

811
00:48:01,800 --> 00:48:02,800
It's only been two weeks.

812
00:48:03,360 --> 00:48:06,200
Do you know how long
my longest mission was?

813
00:48:07,400 --> 00:48:08,400
Eight months.

814
00:48:12,080 --> 00:48:13,080
I know.

815
00:48:15,400 --> 00:48:16,400
Eight months.

816
00:48:17,400 --> 00:48:18,400
Then what?

817
00:48:20,360 --> 00:48:21,360
What happened?

818
00:48:22,000 --> 00:48:23,520
My father died because of you.

819
00:48:23,600 --> 00:48:24,640
The drug dealer escaped.

820
00:48:26,280 --> 00:48:27,336
Do you know I hadn't seen him

821
00:48:27,360 --> 00:48:29,240
for over a year before he died?!

822
00:48:46,000 --> 00:48:47,120
It was all my fault.

823
00:48:48,760 --> 00:48:49,760
I...

824
00:48:51,760 --> 00:48:53,320
You know what I did that day?

825
00:48:54,480 --> 00:48:55,840
I did what you did.

826
00:48:58,480 --> 00:49:00,360
What a cute kid.

827
00:49:01,160 --> 00:49:02,720
I have bubbles right here.

828
00:49:03,720 --> 00:49:05,000
Do you like bubbles? Yes.

829
00:49:05,080 --> 00:49:06,400
Let's play in the van, shall we?

830
00:49:06,480 --> 00:49:08,240
We've got lots of toys inside.

831
00:49:08,320 --> 00:49:09,440
Come with me.

832
00:49:20,120 --> 00:49:21,760
What? Get lost! Put the kid down.

833
00:49:22,360 --> 00:49:23,000
Who are you?

834
00:49:23,040 --> 00:49:24,360
Put the kid down.

835
00:49:24,720 --> 00:49:25,720
Police.

836
00:49:27,040 --> 00:49:28,040
Don't move.

837
00:49:28,680 --> 00:49:29,560
You think you are better than us?

838
00:49:29,640 --> 00:49:30,480
Don't you move.

839
00:49:30,560 --> 00:49:31,360
Let's see your badge.

840
00:49:31,440 --> 00:49:32,320
Shut it, or I'll arrest you.

841
00:49:32,400 --> 00:49:33,400
Police. Freeze.

842
00:50:01,120 --> 00:50:02,120
My recklessness

843
00:50:03,000 --> 00:50:04,440
got your father killed.

844
00:50:10,600 --> 00:50:12,200
But you saved that child.

845
00:50:13,480 --> 00:50:14,480
I didn't.

846
00:50:16,160 --> 00:50:18,840
The traffickers escaped in the chaos.

847
00:50:22,000 --> 00:50:23,960
Did they ever find the child?

848
00:50:26,760 --> 00:50:27,800
I don't know.

849
00:50:39,240 --> 00:50:40,760
As police officers,

850
00:50:41,120 --> 00:50:43,440
we have to learn to stay rational.

851
00:50:43,840 --> 00:50:45,040
Follow discipline.

852
00:50:45,840 --> 00:50:46,920
Execute orders.

853
00:50:48,960 --> 00:50:50,400
Better to have regrets

854
00:50:53,120 --> 00:50:54,200
than to make mistakes.

855
00:50:56,400 --> 00:50:57,920
Because that's our duty.

856
00:51:47,360 --> 00:51:48,240
Possible sighting of the Shadow.

857
00:51:48,320 --> 00:51:49,920
Mercado Rua de Oeste.

858
00:51:49,960 --> 00:51:50,960
Blue sweater jacket.

859
00:51:51,040 --> 00:51:52,440
Grey pants. Wearing a brown beret.

860
00:51:52,840 --> 00:51:53,680
Could be wearing glasses.

861
00:51:53,760 --> 00:51:55,360
Everyone, change outfits.

862
00:51:55,440 --> 00:51:56,440
Prepare to ID him.

863
00:51:59,440 --> 00:52:01,640
All units, be aware.

864
00:52:01,720 --> 00:52:02,720
Shadow spotted.

865
00:52:03,120 --> 00:52:04,240
Monitoring the market.

866
00:52:04,520 --> 00:52:06,200
Adorable Unit en route.

867
00:52:06,840 --> 00:52:07,840
Alpaca, Potsticker, east.

868
00:52:08,200 --> 00:52:09,320
Eggy, Tofu, west.

869
00:52:09,440 --> 00:52:10,640
Lucky, Rice Roll, south.

870
00:52:10,920 --> 00:52:12,000
Pudding, Pork Bun, north.

871
00:52:12,040 --> 00:52:13,680
The Shadow may have seen you before.

872
00:52:13,760 --> 00:52:15,720
A pro like him doesn't forget.

873
00:52:15,840 --> 00:52:17,360
He'll be vigilant the second time

874
00:52:17,440 --> 00:52:18,480
and get suspicious.

875
00:52:18,560 --> 00:52:20,320
Maintain a two-unit distance.

876
00:52:20,840 --> 00:52:21,840
Piggy.

877
00:52:25,160 --> 00:52:27,320
ID him up close.

878
00:52:28,200 --> 00:52:29,480
He hasn't seen your face.

879
00:52:30,200 --> 00:52:32,200
Small suggestion for ground surveillance.

880
00:52:32,280 --> 00:52:34,960
You should use your
most inconspicuous officers.

881
00:52:35,040 --> 00:52:36,840
Preferably ones suspects
haven't seen before.

882
00:52:42,000 --> 00:52:43,000
Go.

883
00:53:00,240 --> 00:53:01,800
Slow down.

884
00:53:02,080 --> 00:53:03,280
Maintain distance.

885
00:53:06,280 --> 00:53:07,680
Doghead calling Animal Paradise.

886
00:53:07,720 --> 00:53:09,560
Adorable Unit's on site.

887
00:53:09,920 --> 00:53:10,640
Alpaca.

888
00:53:10,720 --> 00:53:12,760
Approach the fruit stall on the west.

889
00:53:16,480 --> 00:53:18,040
Walk slowly.

890
00:53:18,240 --> 00:53:19,240
Don't rush.

891
00:53:19,680 --> 00:53:21,880
Our mission is to ID the target.

892
00:53:21,960 --> 00:53:23,920
Don't spook the Shadow.

893
00:53:25,720 --> 00:53:27,960
Relax. Be natural.

894
00:53:28,480 --> 00:53:29,400
He's a pro.

895
00:53:29,480 --> 00:53:30,960
We have no room for negligence.

896
00:53:34,720 --> 00:53:35,760
Potsticker, east exit.

897
00:53:35,840 --> 00:53:36,440
Copy.

898
00:53:36,480 --> 00:53:38,080
Pork Bun, stand by at the footbridge.

899
00:53:38,160 --> 00:53:39,160
Copy.

900
00:53:44,120 --> 00:53:45,360
Pudding, don't get too close.

901
00:53:45,680 --> 00:53:46,800
Walk away.

902
00:53:47,680 --> 00:53:48,480
Alpaca.

903
00:53:48,640 --> 00:53:50,000
Can you ID him?

904
00:53:51,520 --> 00:53:52,520
Negative.

905
00:53:52,560 --> 00:53:53,600
Can't see his face.

906
00:53:53,680 --> 00:53:54,680
Can't confirm.

907
00:54:00,880 --> 00:54:02,240
We may be able to see his face.

908
00:54:08,360 --> 00:54:10,320
Eggy, Shadow might've seen you at Aoxing.

909
00:54:11,520 --> 00:54:12,520
Don't turn.

910
00:54:22,000 --> 00:54:23,200
Tofu, well done.

911
00:54:23,320 --> 00:54:24,640
Piggy, it's on you.

912
00:54:29,280 --> 00:54:30,280
Be careful.

913
00:54:36,640 --> 00:54:37,760
I'll get closer to him.

914
00:54:43,040 --> 00:54:44,720
Piggy, you might get blown.

915
00:54:44,800 --> 00:54:46,240
I know. I have an idea.

916
00:55:19,480 --> 00:55:20,480
It's him.

917
00:55:20,520 --> 00:55:21,520
Confirmed.

918
00:55:22,240 --> 00:55:23,240
Hand down.

919
00:55:31,800 --> 00:55:32,800
Don't move the camera.

920
00:55:48,920 --> 00:55:50,800
All units, positive ID on the Shadow.

921
00:55:51,440 --> 00:55:52,776
Adorable Unit, change and stand by.

922
00:55:52,800 --> 00:55:53,840
Lay low.

923
00:55:54,440 --> 00:55:55,640
Everyone, good job.

924
00:55:58,560 --> 00:56:00,560
Target confirmed.

925
00:56:00,640 --> 00:56:03,760
All units, do not breach
3 blocks perimeter.

926
00:56:03,880 --> 00:56:04,560
I repeat.

927
00:56:04,640 --> 00:56:06,440
Do not approach target area.

928
00:56:06,520 --> 00:56:08,480
Be advised, no siren.

929
00:56:13,120 --> 00:56:14,920
The target has entered a blind spot.

930
00:56:17,160 --> 00:56:18,160
Lucky, you're up.

931
00:56:19,920 --> 00:56:20,920
Potsticker, tail him.

932
00:56:22,320 --> 00:56:23,320
Not too close.

933
00:56:24,840 --> 00:56:26,360
The bastard won't get away.

934
00:56:28,840 --> 00:56:30,440
Shadow's headed to Changning Apartments.

935
00:56:32,440 --> 00:56:34,840
The blocks are connected inside.
There are hundreds of flats.

936
00:56:34,920 --> 00:56:37,560
If we don't get his flat number,
there won't be a next time.

937
00:56:50,360 --> 00:56:52,200
The Shadow's in Block C, Unit 1.

938
00:56:52,280 --> 00:56:53,160
No camera inside the building.

939
00:56:53,240 --> 00:56:54,920
We'll lose him in an elevator.

940
00:56:55,000 --> 00:56:55,760
Pull over.

941
00:56:55,840 --> 00:56:57,056
Adorables. They are too far away.

942
00:56:57,080 --> 00:56:57,960
Adorable unit, come in.

943
00:56:58,040 --> 00:56:59,520
I'm too far away to catch up.

944
00:56:59,600 --> 00:57:00,600
Potsticker cannot follow.

945
00:57:00,960 --> 00:57:01,960
Eggy cannot follow.

946
00:57:02,200 --> 00:57:04,080
I'll go. Piggy can follow.

947
00:57:07,320 --> 00:57:08,320
I'm in.

948
00:58:22,320 --> 00:58:23,320
Top floor.

949
00:58:39,640 --> 00:58:41,560
What are you doing?
Will you listen to me or not?

950
00:58:41,680 --> 00:58:42,280
What?

951
00:58:42,360 --> 00:58:43,200
Dating behind my back.

952
00:58:43,280 --> 00:58:44,680
My friend caught you, you know.

953
00:58:50,800 --> 00:58:51,800
What floor?

954
00:58:53,240 --> 00:58:54,520
I forgot something.

955
00:58:54,600 --> 00:58:55,600
You two go ahead.

956
00:59:12,720 --> 00:59:13,760
Getting all dolled up now?

957
00:59:14,320 --> 00:59:16,160
I knew you'd lose your earrings

958
00:59:16,240 --> 00:59:16,960
with those big earphones on.

959
00:59:17,040 --> 00:59:18,320
C'mon, leave me alone.

960
00:59:20,320 --> 00:59:21,320
See this?

961
00:59:21,440 --> 00:59:23,680
They stop listening when they grow up.

962
00:59:23,880 --> 00:59:25,560
All they do is go against their parents.

963
00:59:27,400 --> 00:59:30,280
They're grown-ups with minds of their own.

964
00:59:31,480 --> 00:59:32,960
What can a father do?

965
00:59:33,400 --> 00:59:34,640
You're terribly open-minded.

966
00:59:34,760 --> 00:59:36,280
Otherwise, they'll start

967
00:59:36,360 --> 00:59:37,920
hiding things from you.

968
00:59:44,920 --> 00:59:47,720
Your nosy aunt said that
guy looks like an alpaca.

969
00:59:47,800 --> 00:59:49,360
Is that why you're hiding him from me?

970
00:59:49,480 --> 00:59:50,480
Who?

971
00:59:51,120 --> 00:59:52,320
The guy you're dating.

972
00:59:52,840 --> 00:59:54,440
What's wrong with looking like a alpaca?

973
00:59:54,480 --> 00:59:55,760
It's fine as long as I like him.

974
00:59:56,560 --> 00:59:57,920
He is more handsome than you too.

975
00:59:59,880 --> 01:00:01,320
Why are you buying rottened apples?

976
01:00:01,400 --> 01:00:02,696
Got a camera signal.
Can you get fresh apples?

977
01:00:02,720 --> 01:00:04,440
It's all the same in the stomach.

978
01:00:05,320 --> 01:00:06,840
Here. Want one?

979
01:00:12,520 --> 01:00:13,696
Check his background. Roger that.

980
01:00:13,720 --> 01:00:14,960
Shadow's face acquired.

981
01:00:15,040 --> 01:00:16,280
Caught on camera.

982
01:00:17,440 --> 01:00:18,960
How can you just spit that out?

983
01:00:19,800 --> 01:00:21,000
The janitors will clean it up.

984
01:00:21,280 --> 01:00:22,320
Look, it's fine.

985
01:00:24,000 --> 01:00:25,600
I hope you'll marry into

986
01:00:25,680 --> 01:00:27,240
a rich family someday.

987
01:00:27,640 --> 01:00:30,240
Ever seen a rich father-in-law
behave this uncivilized?

988
01:00:31,240 --> 01:00:34,440
Maybe that's what the
rich people like about me.

989
01:00:34,560 --> 01:00:35,920
Will you be better to yourself?

990
01:00:36,000 --> 01:00:37,680
Stop buying rottened apples.

991
01:00:37,760 --> 01:00:39,760
I'm saving up for you.

992
01:00:39,840 --> 01:00:40,840
Not again.

993
01:00:44,880 --> 01:00:45,880
Bye.

994
01:00:54,520 --> 01:00:56,320
So who's courting who now?

995
01:00:56,400 --> 01:00:57,400
None of your business.

996
01:00:58,080 --> 01:00:59,160
You have such a bad temper.

997
01:00:59,360 --> 01:01:00,400
What does he see in you?

998
01:01:02,920 --> 01:01:04,120
Keep walking.

999
01:01:04,520 --> 01:01:06,080
I have a great temper.

1000
01:01:07,040 --> 01:01:08,040
Now what?

1001
01:01:08,080 --> 01:01:08,800
Follow me.

1002
01:01:08,880 --> 01:01:10,320
What's his zodiac?

1003
01:01:10,400 --> 01:01:11,600
What's it to you?

1004
01:01:11,680 --> 01:01:13,080
To see if he is compatible with me.

1005
01:01:14,600 --> 01:01:15,440
You're not serious.

1006
01:01:15,520 --> 01:01:18,760
Get the package. Cover me.
I'm amazed how nosy you can be.

1007
01:01:22,240 --> 01:01:23,560
You buy so much stuff.

1008
01:01:23,640 --> 01:01:24,920
Wasting money.

1009
01:01:34,960 --> 01:01:35,800
Police.

1010
01:01:35,880 --> 01:01:36,720
Police business.

1011
01:01:36,800 --> 01:01:38,520
Close the door.

1012
01:01:38,960 --> 01:01:40,720
We need this flat, please move out.

1013
01:01:45,160 --> 01:01:46,160
Eighth floor.

1014
01:02:03,720 --> 01:02:05,200
802, got it.

1015
01:02:05,680 --> 01:02:07,320
Shadow lives in Channing apartment,

1016
01:02:07,400 --> 01:02:10,840
C block, unit 1, 802. Solid intel.

1017
01:02:40,520 --> 01:02:41,520
Pick it up.

1018
01:02:59,880 --> 01:03:01,720
What's that sound? Popping bubble wrap?

1019
01:03:02,280 --> 01:03:03,280
Is it OCD?

1020
01:03:14,440 --> 01:03:15,760
He didn't do this one.

1021
01:03:15,880 --> 01:03:17,440
No wonder it's torn.

1022
01:03:21,760 --> 01:03:22,760
Weird.

1023
01:03:23,240 --> 01:03:24,240
They're all wrong.

1024
01:03:49,000 --> 01:03:52,640
In the past, the Shadow
would always disappear after a job

1025
01:03:52,720 --> 01:03:54,480
and remains silent for a while.

1026
01:03:54,720 --> 01:03:56,040
He's a man of principle.

1027
01:03:56,880 --> 01:03:58,880
This time, he broke his own protocol.

1028
01:03:59,240 --> 01:04:00,240
What's happening?

1029
01:04:01,080 --> 01:04:02,400
If I'm not mistaken,

1030
01:04:03,400 --> 01:04:04,520
my guess is

1031
01:04:04,960 --> 01:04:05,960
we've spooked him.

1032
01:04:06,920 --> 01:04:08,000
Whatever he wants to play,

1033
01:04:08,640 --> 01:04:09,640
we'll play with him.

1034
01:04:17,560 --> 01:04:19,200
Finally stopped buying rotten apples?

1035
01:04:19,720 --> 01:04:20,720
What a coincidence.

1036
01:04:23,920 --> 01:04:24,920
How much?

1037
01:04:25,560 --> 01:04:26,560
$3.70.

1038
01:04:27,080 --> 01:04:28,080
Prices have gone up.

1039
01:04:28,600 --> 01:04:29,800
It's all right.

1040
01:04:29,880 --> 01:04:31,200
Twenty cents.

1041
01:04:31,240 --> 01:04:32,800
Everything's more expensive now.

1042
01:04:32,880 --> 01:04:34,080
This one. Thanks.

1043
01:04:36,680 --> 01:04:37,920
That stall is cheaper.

1044
01:04:38,880 --> 01:04:40,800
Are you joking? They're terrible.

1045
01:04:40,880 --> 01:04:41,920
Nothing fresh.

1046
01:04:43,920 --> 01:04:44,920
I meant

1047
01:04:45,040 --> 01:04:46,600
the fish stall behind it.

1048
01:04:46,680 --> 01:04:47,680
It's cheap.

1049
01:04:48,040 --> 01:04:49,040
You're right.

1050
01:04:49,560 --> 01:04:50,440
Not to mention

1051
01:04:50,520 --> 01:04:52,360
the owner's dad is a good man.

1052
01:04:52,720 --> 01:04:53,720
Ten dollars.

1053
01:04:54,560 --> 01:04:55,560
It's unfortunate

1054
01:04:56,360 --> 01:04:57,680
how sudden he passed.

1055
01:04:57,760 --> 01:04:58,880
Heart attack.

1056
01:04:59,560 --> 01:05:00,560
Asthma.

1057
01:05:04,040 --> 01:05:05,360
Your daughter's all grown up.

1058
01:05:05,440 --> 01:05:06,080
Doesn't she want to move out?

1059
01:05:06,160 --> 01:05:08,960
Her mom left me because of my gambling.

1060
01:05:09,480 --> 01:05:11,560
After her mom died from illness,

1061
01:05:11,880 --> 01:05:13,360
she moved in with me.

1062
01:05:15,360 --> 01:05:16,360
Thanks.

1063
01:05:18,120 --> 01:05:18,880
What are you doing?

1064
01:05:18,960 --> 01:05:20,160
Planning to work in a casino?

1065
01:05:20,400 --> 01:05:21,656
Selling fish doesn't pay the bills

1066
01:05:21,680 --> 01:05:22,760
Give me a grass carp.

1067
01:05:24,840 --> 01:05:26,120
See these calluses?

1068
01:05:27,080 --> 01:05:29,120
Got them from playing
cards when I was young.

1069
01:05:29,200 --> 01:05:30,520
I wanted to be a God of Gamblers.

1070
01:05:31,200 --> 01:05:33,160
I didn't know that was only in the movies.

1071
01:05:34,560 --> 01:05:35,640
I thought

1072
01:05:36,240 --> 01:05:37,840
you got callus from holding guns.

1073
01:05:38,040 --> 01:05:39,480
Never held a gun.

1074
01:05:39,680 --> 01:05:41,800
Held a chef's knife for 10 years, though.

1075
01:05:43,040 --> 01:05:44,720
Let's find a time. I'll cook a few dishes.

1076
01:05:44,800 --> 01:05:45,840
Come over

1077
01:05:46,360 --> 01:05:47,360
and have a drink.

1078
01:05:48,880 --> 01:05:49,880
That's funny.

1079
01:05:50,640 --> 01:05:52,080
I used to be a chef too.

1080
01:05:52,320 --> 01:05:53,760
My teacher was from Hangzhou.

1081
01:05:53,840 --> 01:05:55,640
I make a mean West Lake vinegar fish.

1082
01:05:56,200 --> 01:05:58,720
How about today?

1083
01:06:01,000 --> 01:06:01,720
Great.

1084
01:06:01,960 --> 01:06:04,000
I happen to have a bottle of Chilean wine

1085
01:06:04,640 --> 01:06:05,680
that goes with that dish.

1086
01:06:06,360 --> 01:06:08,160
You bring the wine, I'll cook.

1087
01:06:12,480 --> 01:06:13,480
Come in.

1088
01:06:13,520 --> 01:06:14,520
Have a seat.

1089
01:06:14,800 --> 01:06:16,000
I'll put this into the fridge.

1090
01:06:23,720 --> 01:06:24,560
What was he doing?

1091
01:06:24,640 --> 01:06:25,800
Checking for dust on shelves.

1092
01:06:25,840 --> 01:06:27,440
To see if they just moved in.

1093
01:06:30,560 --> 01:06:31,800
You're not getting away.

1094
01:06:31,880 --> 01:06:33,040
You may be the guest,

1095
01:06:33,080 --> 01:06:35,640
but you're not spared from kitchen duty.
Show us what you've got.

1096
01:06:37,760 --> 01:06:38,880
I can't wait.

1097
01:06:40,960 --> 01:06:42,360
How long were you a chef for?

1098
01:06:42,880 --> 01:06:44,320
Over ten years.

1099
01:06:45,440 --> 01:06:46,600
And that's the knife you use?

1100
01:07:05,720 --> 01:07:07,080
You know your knives.

1101
01:07:07,240 --> 01:07:08,400
I just like

1102
01:07:08,680 --> 01:07:10,160
doing things the right way.

1103
01:07:11,840 --> 01:07:12,840
Got any kids?

1104
01:07:14,280 --> 01:07:15,280
I'm on my own.

1105
01:07:15,440 --> 01:07:16,920
A lonely old man.

1106
01:07:17,240 --> 01:07:19,560
Here's a home-cooked meal.

1107
01:07:23,040 --> 01:07:24,760
Your girl seems like a smart kid.

1108
01:07:25,440 --> 01:07:26,880
That scar on her forehead...

1109
01:07:26,920 --> 01:07:27,920
How'd she get it?

1110
01:07:35,880 --> 01:07:37,840
Put that phone away.

1111
01:07:37,960 --> 01:07:38,976
Talk with our guest instead.

1112
01:07:39,000 --> 01:07:40,000
Okay.

1113
01:07:40,400 --> 01:07:41,400
I need the bathroom.

1114
01:07:46,400 --> 01:07:48,080
If I had a child,

1115
01:07:48,160 --> 01:07:50,800
I'd ban phones from the dinner table, too.

1116
01:07:55,120 --> 01:07:56,360
Start cloning.

1117
01:07:56,840 --> 01:07:58,280
What are you studying?

1118
01:07:58,480 --> 01:07:59,480
Nursing.

1119
01:07:59,600 --> 01:08:01,520
You plan to be a nurse after graduation?

1120
01:08:03,560 --> 01:08:05,200
Maybe in a retirement home.

1121
01:08:06,360 --> 01:08:07,480
What a kind heart.

1122
01:08:10,640 --> 01:08:12,240
How'd you get that scar?

1123
01:08:12,320 --> 01:08:13,320
This one?

1124
01:08:16,120 --> 01:08:17,439
Fifth grade.

1125
01:08:18,040 --> 01:08:19,800
Got into a fight with some girls.

1126
01:08:20,640 --> 01:08:21,880
Why were you fighting?

1127
01:08:22,200 --> 01:08:23,439
A classmate was being bullied.

1128
01:08:23,520 --> 01:08:24,880
Couldn't stand idly by.

1129
01:08:25,120 --> 01:08:27,160
But I never told anyone that until now.

1130
01:08:29,800 --> 01:08:31,120
Does your dad know?

1131
01:08:31,200 --> 01:08:32,800
He couldn't possibly know.

1132
01:08:33,840 --> 01:08:35,200
That's odd.

1133
01:08:36,240 --> 01:08:37,240
What's up?

1134
01:08:38,760 --> 01:08:40,560
How'd she get that scar again?

1135
01:08:41,760 --> 01:08:43,640
She got into a fight in fifth grade.

1136
01:08:43,680 --> 01:08:44,680
One against five.

1137
01:08:44,920 --> 01:08:46,680
Someone bashed her with a bottle.

1138
01:08:50,240 --> 01:08:51,880
I never told anyone.

1139
01:08:53,359 --> 01:08:54,560
Not even my mom.

1140
01:08:55,520 --> 01:08:56,840
You didn't tell her because

1141
01:08:56,920 --> 01:08:58,080
you didn't want her to worry.

1142
01:08:58,240 --> 01:09:00,800
Even your teacher thought you hit a door.

1143
01:09:00,880 --> 01:09:01,880
Right?

1144
01:09:04,479 --> 01:09:05,640
How'd you know, then?

1145
01:09:11,439 --> 01:09:13,160
After our divorce,

1146
01:09:14,040 --> 01:09:15,040
my debts

1147
01:09:15,720 --> 01:09:16,800
made me some enemies.

1148
01:09:18,479 --> 01:09:19,840
I was worried they'd hurt you.

1149
01:09:23,279 --> 01:09:24,279
The truth is...

1150
01:09:25,840 --> 01:09:27,200
I was always nearby.

1151
01:09:35,720 --> 01:09:36,720
See?

1152
01:09:38,920 --> 01:09:40,399
That's a dad.

1153
01:09:46,640 --> 01:09:48,160
Then why didn't you help me?

1154
01:09:48,240 --> 01:09:49,319
Help you?

1155
01:09:49,439 --> 01:09:51,040
Remember what you did to those girls?

1156
01:09:51,279 --> 01:09:52,279
It's horrifying.

1157
01:09:52,359 --> 01:09:53,760
I was too scared to step in.

1158
01:09:53,800 --> 01:09:55,760
Give me some credit.

1159
01:09:55,880 --> 01:09:56,760
I was standing up for someone.

1160
01:09:56,840 --> 01:09:58,000
You were... What?

1161
01:09:58,120 --> 01:09:59,560
You were committing murder.

1162
01:10:00,200 --> 01:10:01,960
C'mon now. I'm so moved.

1163
01:10:02,040 --> 01:10:04,280
You're embarrassing me.

1164
01:10:21,640 --> 01:10:22,640
How'd it go?

1165
01:10:26,080 --> 01:10:27,080
Go on.

1166
01:10:27,240 --> 01:10:28,240
Smart girl.

1167
01:10:31,200 --> 01:10:32,200
Thank you.

1168
01:10:33,080 --> 01:10:34,080
What for?

1169
01:10:35,840 --> 01:10:37,240
For protecting us.

1170
01:10:45,040 --> 01:10:46,040
Some things

1171
01:10:47,200 --> 01:10:48,680
can never be mended.

1172
01:10:51,080 --> 01:10:53,040
The only thing I could do for your father

1173
01:10:55,000 --> 01:10:56,200
was to watch over you.

1174
01:10:58,800 --> 01:11:00,680
I know you've been worrying about me.

1175
01:11:02,240 --> 01:11:03,240
You want to protect me.

1176
01:11:06,080 --> 01:11:07,560
But I've grown up.

1177
01:11:09,440 --> 01:11:10,440
I'll be okay.

1178
01:11:15,600 --> 01:11:16,600
You're okay.

1179
01:11:19,440 --> 01:11:20,200
Big Brother...

1180
01:11:20,280 --> 01:11:21,440
If you fail,

1181
01:11:21,640 --> 01:11:22,640
what happens next

1182
01:11:22,720 --> 01:11:23,760
will be my call.

1183
01:11:24,760 --> 01:11:25,840
If we do it your way,

1184
01:11:26,280 --> 01:11:27,720
there's no turning back for us.

1185
01:11:28,120 --> 01:11:29,120
I just want to

1186
01:11:30,000 --> 01:11:31,200
do things the right way.

1187
01:11:38,000 --> 01:11:38,800
They have anti-tracking.

1188
01:11:39,000 --> 01:11:40,000
Must be that hacker.

1189
01:11:40,120 --> 01:11:41,120
Stand down.

1190
01:11:43,520 --> 01:11:45,520
Have you checked their background?

1191
01:11:48,520 --> 01:11:49,520
I have.

1192
01:11:53,640 --> 01:11:55,000
What? Forgot something?

1193
01:12:05,320 --> 01:12:06,480
Nothing to worry about.

1194
01:12:07,240 --> 01:12:08,760
Maybe I did think too much.

1195
01:12:15,240 --> 01:12:16,240
Think too much?

1196
01:12:16,360 --> 01:12:17,440
Too much about what?

1197
01:12:38,560 --> 01:12:39,760
I realize that

1198
01:12:40,440 --> 01:12:41,440
you're big boys now.

1199
01:12:42,120 --> 01:12:43,400
It really is time to let go.

1200
01:13:18,840 --> 01:13:20,280
Let's follow through with your plan.

1201
01:13:20,560 --> 01:13:21,560
Got it.

1202
01:13:21,760 --> 01:13:22,840
You know what you're doing?

1203
01:13:28,080 --> 01:13:29,080
I do.

1204
01:14:16,960 --> 01:14:18,720
That girl isn't Guoguo.

1205
01:14:18,800 --> 01:14:19,800
What do you mean?

1206
01:14:20,200 --> 01:14:21,456
There's something wrong with this feed.

1207
01:14:21,480 --> 01:14:22,640
That's definitely not Qiuguo.

1208
01:14:27,440 --> 01:14:28,640
Send backup to Wong.

1209
01:14:28,720 --> 01:14:29,840
He's in danger.

1210
01:14:30,520 --> 01:14:31,600
Cops are coming, leave.

1211
01:15:02,600 --> 01:15:03,600
I failed.

1212
01:15:03,720 --> 01:15:04,720
I'll find another way.

1213
01:15:26,880 --> 01:15:27,880
Hey.

1214
01:15:27,920 --> 01:15:29,120
Has the Shadow moved?

1215
01:15:30,000 --> 01:15:31,360
Nope, all quiet.

1216
01:15:37,480 --> 01:15:39,200
You had your chance, Xiwang.

1217
01:15:43,840 --> 01:15:44,920
Those boys

1218
01:15:45,000 --> 01:15:46,800
didn't even tell the Shadow

1219
01:15:46,880 --> 01:15:48,040
that he's being watched.

1220
01:15:49,920 --> 01:15:52,360
They know we'd use
the Shadow to track them,

1221
01:15:52,440 --> 01:15:53,440
so we wouldn't touch him.

1222
01:15:58,680 --> 01:15:59,400
Right.

1223
01:15:59,480 --> 01:16:01,200
Killing me and creating chaos

1224
01:16:01,600 --> 01:16:04,040
would've created an opening
to break The Shadow out.

1225
01:16:04,440 --> 01:16:05,440
After failing this time,

1226
01:16:05,760 --> 01:16:07,080
they'll look for another chance.

1227
01:16:11,080 --> 01:16:13,320
Their chance is our opportunity, too.

1228
01:16:13,440 --> 01:16:15,080
We have to nail this gang of thieves

1229
01:16:15,160 --> 01:16:16,160
once for all.

1230
01:16:40,000 --> 01:16:41,000
Shadow's on the move.

1231
01:16:53,280 --> 01:16:54,280
Freeze.

1232
01:16:57,480 --> 01:16:58,720
Surveillance team, spread out.

1233
01:17:01,200 --> 01:17:02,480
Madam, that's the same taxi

1234
01:17:02,560 --> 01:17:04,080
as the one at Aoxing.

1235
01:17:04,160 --> 01:17:06,280
Sending photo to the surveillance team now.

1236
01:17:06,360 --> 01:17:07,280
We're standing by.

1237
01:17:07,360 --> 01:17:08,616
When the suspects' location is locked,

1238
01:17:08,640 --> 01:17:09,640
we're ready to move in.

1239
01:17:14,400 --> 01:17:16,440
Target vehicle is approaching our HQ.

1240
01:17:16,520 --> 01:17:17,760
Are they turning themselves in?

1241
01:17:19,200 --> 01:17:20,720
Doesn't look like it.

1242
01:17:27,440 --> 01:17:28,440
Wait.

1243
01:17:28,880 --> 01:17:30,440
Show me that cabinet again.

1244
01:17:36,520 --> 01:17:38,240
Why is that still there?

1245
01:17:40,920 --> 01:17:42,440
He didn't do this one.

1246
01:17:42,960 --> 01:17:43,960
They're all wrong.

1247
01:17:47,880 --> 01:17:49,160
Zoom in and show me again.

1248
01:17:56,720 --> 01:17:57,480
What's that?

1249
01:17:57,560 --> 01:17:59,040
It seems Wong's van has been hit.

1250
01:18:26,080 --> 01:18:27,080
Officer Wong?

1251
01:18:27,160 --> 01:18:28,240
Wong, can you hear me?

1252
01:18:28,480 --> 01:18:30,200
Wong, come in if you hear me.

1253
01:18:30,520 --> 01:18:31,320
Officer Wong?

1254
01:18:31,400 --> 01:18:32,240
Officer Wong?

1255
01:18:32,320 --> 01:18:33,960
Officer Wong? Guoguo.

1256
01:18:34,120 --> 01:18:35,800
Their... Their vehicles broke in.

1257
01:18:36,320 --> 01:18:37,320
Whose vehicles?

1258
01:18:48,120 --> 01:18:48,960
HQ is under attack?

1259
01:18:49,040 --> 01:18:50,040
Madam, what's going on?

1260
01:18:58,160 --> 01:19:00,200
Du Ping, ready the mobile command unit.
Yes, ma'am.

1261
01:19:00,360 --> 01:19:02,160
Surveillance, stay focused. Eyes on target.

1262
01:19:02,240 --> 01:19:03,520
Watch the Shadow's every move.

1263
01:19:11,480 --> 01:19:12,480
Officer Wong.

1264
01:19:15,640 --> 01:19:17,320
Someone's still alive.

1265
01:19:17,480 --> 01:19:18,480
Terminate.

1266
01:19:54,760 --> 01:19:55,760
The phone...

1267
01:19:56,360 --> 01:19:56,920
It's smashed.

1268
01:19:57,000 --> 01:19:58,640
The key to the puzzle isn't the numbers.

1269
01:19:58,720 --> 01:19:59,720
It's the positions.

1270
01:19:59,760 --> 01:20:00,800
They're using Braille.

1271
01:20:00,880 --> 01:20:01,896
The bubble wrap is also Braille.

1272
01:20:01,920 --> 01:20:03,680
Get Intelligence to decipher the messages.

1273
01:20:03,760 --> 01:20:05,520
Find out what they're up to.

1274
01:20:12,280 --> 01:20:13,616
Find a phone, I'll hold them back.

1275
01:20:13,640 --> 01:20:14,640
Go.

1276
01:20:22,640 --> 01:20:23,640
What's this place?

1277
01:20:24,120 --> 01:20:25,560
Looks like an abandoned orphanage.

1278
01:20:25,640 --> 01:20:26,920
No other suspect in sight.

1279
01:20:29,520 --> 01:20:30,760
Use thermal to follow Shadow.

1280
01:20:30,840 --> 01:20:32,160
I need eyes on the inside.

1281
01:20:43,920 --> 01:20:44,720
Captain.

1282
01:20:44,800 --> 01:20:45,840
In the orphanage!

1283
01:20:50,360 --> 01:20:51,080
HQ.

1284
01:20:51,160 --> 01:20:52,560
This is Alpaca. Can anyone hear me?

1285
01:20:53,760 --> 01:20:54,760
Command central?

1286
01:20:54,960 --> 01:20:56,720
We've lost all comms. Command central?

1287
01:21:23,840 --> 01:21:25,560
Brothers, get to work.

1288
01:21:53,760 --> 01:21:55,280
Chop him up.

1289
01:22:26,560 --> 01:22:28,880
Do you know how many cops came after me?

1290
01:22:29,600 --> 01:22:31,080
Two hundred.

1291
01:22:31,400 --> 01:22:32,400
If I took off,

1292
01:22:32,720 --> 01:22:33,840
I'd be dead for sure.

1293
01:22:34,240 --> 01:22:35,240
So what did you do?

1294
01:22:36,240 --> 01:22:38,120
The idiot who got nailed

1295
01:22:38,200 --> 01:22:39,240
became bait.

1296
01:22:41,080 --> 01:22:42,880
Then I took out the biggest threat

1297
01:22:42,960 --> 01:22:44,600
in the Police Force.

1298
01:22:46,080 --> 01:22:48,240
That took out the cops' eyes.

1299
01:22:51,320 --> 01:22:53,840
Then I took out the idiot,

1300
01:22:56,200 --> 01:22:58,680
cutting off the cops' ears, too.

1301
01:22:59,160 --> 01:23:02,680
I've become the idiot in my boys' eyes.

1302
01:23:06,360 --> 01:23:07,360
However

1303
01:23:08,280 --> 01:23:10,560
first you need to be sure to have

1304
01:23:11,640 --> 01:23:12,640
what it takes.

1305
01:23:14,760 --> 01:23:15,920
You're big boys now.

1306
01:23:17,040 --> 01:23:18,120
You know what you're doing?

1307
01:23:21,160 --> 01:23:23,080
Do you?

1308
01:23:23,320 --> 01:23:24,320
Kill him.

1309
01:23:37,640 --> 01:23:39,040
Cell signal's jammed.

1310
01:23:39,120 --> 01:23:40,640
Find a sat phone to call for backup.

1311
01:23:40,720 --> 01:23:42,000
We'll go buy some time.

1312
01:24:10,560 --> 01:24:11,920
That's him.

1313
01:24:12,320 --> 01:24:13,400
Gotta kill him to get paid.

1314
01:24:42,080 --> 01:24:43,416
The Shadow sends messages via Braille.

1315
01:24:43,440 --> 01:24:45,016
The bubble wrap and sudoku are all Braille.

1316
01:24:45,040 --> 01:24:46,600
Guoguo. Give that intel to Madam Wang.

1317
01:24:50,920 --> 01:24:51,920
Guoguo.

1318
01:25:34,440 --> 01:25:37,000
How did the cops arrive so quickly?

1319
01:26:01,000 --> 01:26:02,160
Madam, we've got this.

1320
01:26:45,720 --> 01:26:46,720
Godfather.

1321
01:26:51,400 --> 01:26:52,240
I failed.

1322
01:26:52,360 --> 01:26:53,080
I'll find another way.

1323
01:26:53,160 --> 01:26:54,760
You had your chance, Xiwang.

1324
01:26:55,480 --> 01:26:57,520
If we're the ones nailed by the police,

1325
01:26:58,280 --> 01:26:59,320
what would the old man do?

1326
01:27:00,040 --> 01:27:01,080
This is no one's fault.

1327
01:27:01,160 --> 01:27:02,160
It's just

1328
01:27:02,560 --> 01:27:03,880
carelessness and bad luck.

1329
01:27:06,160 --> 01:27:07,480
Simon's idea?

1330
01:27:07,760 --> 01:27:08,760
Mine.

1331
01:27:20,680 --> 01:27:22,360
Still think you're not like me?

1332
01:27:26,720 --> 01:27:28,200
Xiwang, what are you doing?

1333
01:27:28,320 --> 01:27:29,320
You don't understand

1334
01:27:29,720 --> 01:27:30,960
how dangerous this man is.

1335
01:27:40,600 --> 01:27:42,520
Leave. This isn't part of the plan.

1336
01:27:47,320 --> 01:27:48,920
The old man has to die here

1337
01:27:48,960 --> 01:27:49,800
for you to be safe.

1338
01:27:49,880 --> 01:27:52,240
Leave. This isn't part of the plan.

1339
01:27:52,360 --> 01:27:53,360
Xiwang!

1340
01:27:55,760 --> 01:27:57,160
This was always my plan.

1341
01:28:01,800 --> 01:28:03,440
I'm taking care of you for the last time.

1342
01:28:05,280 --> 01:28:06,440
Last time taking care of me?

1343
01:28:06,520 --> 01:28:07,800
Simon's my little brother.

1344
01:28:08,040 --> 01:28:09,040
If he screws up...

1345
01:28:09,280 --> 01:28:10,280
It's my job to fix it.

1346
01:28:10,360 --> 01:28:11,360
I have no choice.

1347
01:28:15,120 --> 01:28:16,360
Then I'll send you on your way.

1348
01:28:18,440 --> 01:28:19,480
Godfather.

1349
01:28:21,960 --> 01:28:22,960
Your life

1350
01:28:23,760 --> 01:28:24,880
ends here too.

1351
01:29:41,560 --> 01:29:42,560
Get ready.

1352
01:30:59,640 --> 01:31:00,640
He's a wolf.

1353
01:31:01,280 --> 01:31:02,720
We're only wolf pups.

1354
01:31:05,520 --> 01:31:06,520
He's our father.

1355
01:31:10,400 --> 01:31:11,720
In my next life,

1356
01:31:14,400 --> 01:31:16,040
I'll be your real son.

1357
01:32:05,280 --> 01:32:07,520
Get off me!

1358
01:32:08,720 --> 01:32:10,800
Don't move.

1359
01:32:17,720 --> 01:32:18,840
Take care of them.

1360
01:32:19,400 --> 01:32:20,640
Look after their families.

1361
01:32:23,040 --> 01:32:24,040
Yes, sir.

1362
01:32:39,360 --> 01:32:40,360
Gundam, it's me.

1363
01:32:43,040 --> 01:32:44,400
Gundam is my codename.

1364
01:32:44,480 --> 01:32:45,560
What do we know?

1365
01:32:46,920 --> 01:32:48,016
I just contacted Captain Wu.

1366
01:32:48,040 --> 01:32:49,296
A big explosion at the orphanage.

1367
01:32:49,320 --> 01:32:50,760
The Shadow? Not sure.

1368
01:32:50,880 --> 01:32:52,440
But we've ID'd the assailants.

1369
01:32:52,520 --> 01:32:53,360
On the surface,

1370
01:32:53,440 --> 01:32:55,040
they're private security

1371
01:32:55,120 --> 01:32:56,480
for VIP clients at casinos.

1372
01:32:56,880 --> 01:32:58,296
But they also moonlight as mercenaries,

1373
01:32:58,320 --> 01:33:00,040
taking high-risk jobs on the dark web.

1374
01:33:00,120 --> 01:33:01,720
Alpaca contacted Forensics

1375
01:33:01,800 --> 01:33:02,936
after receiving Piggy's message.

1376
01:33:02,960 --> 01:33:05,160
We'll have the results soon, thanks to him.

1377
01:33:08,080 --> 01:33:09,120
It's Gordon D.

1378
01:33:11,480 --> 01:33:12,640
Why is Duan's HK$10 billion

1379
01:33:12,720 --> 01:33:14,400
in the police station's server?

1380
01:33:14,600 --> 01:33:15,840
Without the decryption keys,

1381
01:33:15,920 --> 01:33:17,960
the loot can only be
kept as digital evidence.

1382
01:33:18,040 --> 01:33:19,576
The only way to access the cold wallet
is by using its digital key,

1383
01:33:19,600 --> 01:33:21,400
enabling the 12-word pass phrase

1384
01:33:21,480 --> 01:33:23,800
to be inputted with nanosecond precision.

1385
01:33:24,640 --> 01:33:25,640
They were here.

1386
01:33:28,960 --> 01:33:30,400
Madam, leave this to us.

1387
01:33:30,840 --> 01:33:31,840
Be careful.

1388
01:33:34,520 --> 01:33:35,920
We received a report of a robbery,

1389
01:33:36,040 --> 01:33:36,800
the thieves just left.

1390
01:33:36,880 --> 01:33:38,800
Four males, all in early 20s.

1391
01:33:40,240 --> 01:33:41,640
It was those SWAT guys just now.

1392
01:33:42,440 --> 01:33:43,600
The perps cut the power to

1393
01:33:43,880 --> 01:33:45,000
stop us from

1394
01:33:45,080 --> 01:33:46,400
shutting the hacker out remotely.

1395
01:33:46,600 --> 01:33:49,040
They need a local network within range
to access the servers.

1396
01:33:49,600 --> 01:33:50,600
What does that mean?

1397
01:33:51,480 --> 01:33:52,840
The hacker was just here.

1398
01:34:02,760 --> 01:34:03,760
We were wrong.

1399
01:34:05,840 --> 01:34:06,840
What did we do wrong?

1400
01:34:07,120 --> 01:34:08,520
The old man got himself caught.

1401
01:34:09,960 --> 01:34:11,200
Like an idiot.

1402
01:34:11,920 --> 01:34:13,520
He was outsmarted by the cops.

1403
01:34:16,440 --> 01:34:18,200
That cop's house was too clean.

1404
01:34:18,360 --> 01:34:19,416
It didn't even have a router.

1405
01:34:19,440 --> 01:34:20,480
It was absurd.

1406
01:34:21,480 --> 01:34:23,080
No way the old man didn't notice.

1407
01:34:24,040 --> 01:34:25,600
But he still played along.

1408
01:34:26,400 --> 01:34:28,280
What are you trying to say?

1409
01:34:31,120 --> 01:34:32,120
I think

1410
01:34:33,280 --> 01:34:34,440
he was actually throwing

1411
01:34:34,560 --> 01:34:35,560
